Tribal armed groups have killed more than 100 people in the Democratic Republic of Congo's east, sending hundreds of thousands of people across the border to Uganda. Some are crossing Lake Albert to reach safety there. But it's only the latest flare-up in violence, as the newest Congolese join the 100 000 already there from the same conflict that started years ago.  Former DR Congo VP Bemba returns to Kinshasa Former Congolese vice-president and opposition leader Jean-Pierre Bemba makes his second comeback to Kinshasa since his conviction was overturned in June 2018 by the International Criminal Court, after spending over 10 years in prison. He will add...